laboratory_examinations.findings: Significantly increased blood-flow, blood-pool, and delayed-phase radioactivity over both feet compatible with clinically indicated Reflex Sympathetic Dystrophy (RSD).
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Follow-up three-phase bone scintigraphy showed less diffuse radioactivity over the feet than did the previous study after calcitonin therapy.

laboratory_examinations.findings: Blood urea nitrogen level: 275 mg/dL; Creatinine concentration: 19.9 mg/dL; Hyperkalemia: 6.5 mEq/L; Serum creatine phosphokinase value: 10,970 IU/L.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Values were restored to their normal ranges after hemodialysis.

laboratory_examinations.findings: No resting potential, giant potentials, or an increase of polyphasic wave in the legs.
Prolonged distal latencies and conduction velocity in both tibial, peroneal, and sural nerves.
